node.text: Had a great time in Red Rocks this weekend with @jparmesan. So psyched to be climbing more often and stronger than I have in years. Climbing has never stopped being a big part of my life, but because of injuries I hadn’t  really been able to push myself like I wanted to. But I’m training smarter and harder and it’s paying off!
Last week I adopted my first cat, and I love her. Haven’t landed on a name yet, but I’m thinking Lucca. #cat #tabbycat

Last minute trip to Milan to see Vampire Weekend!!! Didn’t know they were playing until only a couple days ago, but I’m so glad I got to see it. A wonderful way to wrap up my time here in Italy.
Anyone need any school supplies while I’m in Diagon Alley?

My cover of “There Is a Light That Never goes out,” by The Smiths. One of my favorite songs by one of my favorite artists. Please like the Hopalong Cassidy Instagram tagged in this post!! To hear the full song, and the rest of the ep, head here: https://hopalongcassidy.bandcamp.com/album/selected-covers-a-ukulele-ep

Hi friends. I made an EP of cover songs on my ukulele and I'm very excited to share it! Here is the song "Dammit," by Blink-182. When I moved to Italy one of my goals was to focus on my creativity, and this is the first finished project! I can't wait to hear what you think. Please like the page and check out the full EP here: https://hopalongcassidy.bandcamp.com/…/selected-covers-a-uk…
You can download it for free!! And like the Instagram page, tagged in pic
